<span id="freeTextContainer15757786994898494512">There are two parts to this novel that are very hard to reconcile. <br/>The first element is an amazing fiction (it was contemporary at the time it was written, although now I&apos;d consider it historical fiction) filled with religious imagery, fabulous thoughts on the Red Scare, the effect of a treason charge on the children of the person, our government&apos;s culpability, and the legal process. I&apos;d give this part of the novel 4 stars<br/>The second part was that this novel is extremely cruel, violent, and misog</span>
  <span id="freeText15757786994898494512" style="display:none">There are two parts to this novel that are very hard to reconcile. <br />The first element is an amazing fiction (it was contemporary at the time it was written, although now I'd consider it historical fiction) filled with religious imagery, fabulous thoughts on the Red Scare, the effect of a treason charge on the children of the person, our government's culpability, and the legal process. I'd give this part of the novel 4 stars<br />The second part was that this novel is extremely cruel, violent, and misogynistic. This part gets a star, maybe.<br />How do you reconcile the two? Judicious skimming is definitely recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15757786994898494512" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

