    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_17511954" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/17511954" />
    <a title="Dan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/929972-dan"><img alt="Dan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1267461501p2/929972.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/17511954?book_show_action=true">Mar 11, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dan" href="/user/show/929972-dan">Dan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/929972-dan?shelf=novels">novels</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer17511954" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer348264487270539543">This novel is a comment on the shifts in progressive politics in America in the mid-twentieth century. In the late 60s, a graduate student writes a dissertation on execution; the dissertation has particularly personal meaning for the student, whose parents were executed as spies in the early 50s (the parents are based partly on Julius and Ethel Rosenberg, who were electrocuted in 1953).</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

