<div id="review_3017237965" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3017237965" />
    <a title="Owain Talfryn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/94942789-owain-talfryn"><img alt="Owain Talfryn" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3017237965?book_show_action=true">Oct 20, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Owain Talfryn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Owain Talfryn" href="/user/show/94942789-owain-talfryn">Owain Talfryn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780141188188" href="/book/show/637716.The_Book_of_Daniel">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3017237965" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7288041377518476660">Occasionally excellent, sometimes tedious, the novel is at its best when Daniel confronts the injustice of American capitalism with a barely contained rage, always edging towards breakdown. Some moments were genuinely powerful but wasn&apos;t a fan of the (mostly) unchecked misogyny on display.</span>
  <span id="freeText7288041377518476660" style="display:none">Occasionally excellent, sometimes tedious, the novel is at its best when Daniel confronts the injustice of American capitalism with a barely contained rage, always edging towards breakdown. Some moments were genuinely powerful but wasn't a fan of the (mostly) unchecked misogyny on display.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7288041377518476660" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


